	)
	(text "OE is an active‑LOW input.\nWhen HIGH, all outputs are disabled (tristated or forced to a defined state you program).\nWhen LOW, outputs operate normally.\nCan also feed a fast PWM signal to globally dim or blink all LEDs simultaneously, without sending I²C commands."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 49.276 118.364 0)
		(effects
